body:
When using go code to generate rest api, it is beneficial to put them raml definitions of the api into the source code for the package implementing the rest api.

Issuing command: 'go doc -raml myservice' on a package with source code like this:

// RAML:
// baseUri: http://mydomain.github.io/myservice  
// title: MYSERVICE
// /projects:
//   /{project}:
//     /dependencies
//       /{dependency}: 

should produce output:

baseUri: http://mydomain.github.io/myservice
title: MYSERVICE
/projects:
  /{project}:
    /dependencies
      /{dependency}:
